How the mattress and the somier are chosen: women and men are looking for different things
Nothing of a pompous frame for the bed; what really confers its quality to a good bed is the surface to lie down, that is, the mattress and the somier.
First of all, they must be perfectly complemented so that they adapt to specific users.
During the election, numerous elements come into play, including the weight, height, health status and the owner's sex.
Also important is the type of interior in which the mattress and somier are located.
A typical example?
For example, in a weekend cabin that doesn't usually have heating, latex mattresses shouldn't be used because they "heat" more slowly.
In addition, they tend to weigh considerably more than the usual polyurethane mattresses.
Therefore, it is necessary to turn them around more frequently.
If the central channels are not properly aired and, above, they are on a firm basis, they keep moisture inside. It may even appear mold underneath.
When choosing a bed, customs also influence.
Anyone who has spent a lot of time abroad often uses a very high mattress with a soft layer and will have trouble feeling good on a lower and harder surface.
"Almost all the hockey players who came back from the NHL complained that they didn't sleep as well here.""
"For their crushed shoulders, heels and hips needed mattresses with a soft layer of viscoelastic."
"This type of mattress is also recommended for people with diabetes that has long problems of the nervous system, so they receive bad information from the joints and skin," explains Sylva Hadamcziková, who specializes in padded furniture.
Many hockey players, like other customers, have long preferred viscoelastic mattresses.
"There is no problem today, because they have these proper Tempur and the Italian Magniflex, but also the Czech Tropico brand."
You don't have to be an NHL player anymore to be able to appreciate the viscoelastic.
This "miracle" works in a very simple way.
Optimizes its stiffness and shapes depending on the absorbed heat or adapts to your body heat.
Nothing puts pressure on the night, it won't turn around like after a tough game.
Just, he's getting better.
Vicoelastic also functions as protection against sores.
When choosing the size of the mattress, add the length of your feet to your height, i.e. between 21 and 34 cm.
A man or woman with a height of about 180 cm will need a bed of between 210 and 220 cm.
The minimum width for a person should be, in a double room, 90 cm, in total 180 cm.
In the case of single rooms, for example singles, at least 120 to 140 cm is recommended.
So that a possible visit is comfortable, too.
"If not, you can apply a simple standard to calculate the width: by lying face up, you should have your hands comfortably shrugged towards the elbows," advises engineer Helena Prokopová, expert at Cechu "alouní" a dekoratér, who has been dealing for many years with the problem of healthy sleep and the ergonomics of furniture, a subject she teaches in specialized schools.
In the double rooms, each needs its own somber and mattress, so during the purchase you have to pay attention to combine the height of the mattresses.
Otherwise, it will be necessary to ride the somieres at different heights, which is not always possible in all beds.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, models with dock interiors a minimum of 15 cm, of which at least three centimeters are for the layer that adapts to the shapes and softens.
"By touching it with your hand or by settling on the mattress, you certainly shouldn't notice the docks," warns Helena Prokopová.
Each mattress requires a certain type of somier.
The fully padded bedrooms, where the mattress and base are like siamese, make no sense in the bedroom.
The mattresses breathe badly and you can't wash your holster, which is often done today.
And, since every night we sweat between 0.2 and 0.75 l of sweat, it is clear that after about five or seven years the mattress will begin to remind us of a large (and congested) sieve.
For this reason, specialists reject slogans that speak of a mattress life of up to 25 years or even a lifetime guarantee.
However, everything has a pero.
Therefore, the sellers give advice: on the mattresses with a width of 120 or 140 cm, take care of the cleaning and washing of the case, but better add a mattress protector that can be easily removed and washed.
Although mattress cases with zip closure are currently manufactured throughout their perimeter, so when they open they stay in two parts (something very important for washing and the size of the washing machine), their manipulation in the larger models (and for a single person) when lifting the mattress can seem like a fight between a flyweight and a heavy weight.
On the bed, instead of a somier, does he have a firm board?
Never.
At most for beds designed for visits to spend one night.
However, you should make (if you don't already have) ventilation holes on the board and should be used with a mattress with springs inside and a minimum height of 15 cm with the docks in bags (like the German Taschenfederkern) and a soft layer.
Polyurethane mattresses should not be used on such bases.
For non-entangible sheet sommys containing between 14 and 18 sheets, latex mattresses or sandwich mattresses (e.g. a combination of latex and coconut fiber) can be used, although a sommier with a greater number of sheets, 28 or more, in which the sheets of the lumbar area are reinforced and your rigidity can be regulated.
The joint foil somieres should not be used with a spring mattress, as it does not react to reclining.
In addition to the adjustment of the stiffness of the sheets, shoulder protection can also be used.
This is a special fixation of the sheets that allows you to press or even tilt the sheets in such a way that they "surround" perfectly to the shoulders during sleep.
For men who have very wide shoulders, it's a very important thing.
They even remember the mattress manufacturers who, in the "masculine," began to use a softer area precisely around the shoulders.
They also remember women, for whom they put a softer area around the hips.
For the most demanding customers, there are somieres with cross or tablet structure with the so-called multi-stortion damping.
The pressure is distributed between different points and the tension is reduced.
You should also keep in mind that, even if you use the right mattress and solpler, if you use a bad pillow (large and "mullida"), most of the advantages will disappear.
The basic standard is simple: the pillow must hold the head and the corners can only reach the shoulders, so that the muscles of the shoulders can relax.
The recommended suitable size is 50 x 60 cm, something normal for example in Scandinavia.
When lying on the side, the pillow should be on the same level (when combined with the somier with shoulder reinforcement or the softer area of the mattress) as the shoulder height.
Modern mattresses have something to do with the original mattresses stuffed with straw stuffing.
Manufacturers continue to use natural materials or at least mixtures more and more often.
In fact, biological mattresses are fashionable.
Oil-based raw materials, with which polyurethane foam is manufactured, are filled with natural oils, such as castor or soybeans.
In fact, virtually all known manufacturers use soybeans.
"Biological, in the case of mattresses, means that the center is made only of materials of natural origin," explains Petr Vasí-ek of the company Tropico Plus.
Natural substances are also used during the manufacture of the mattress case, one of the first aloe vera.
But you can also opt for microcapsules, which release a fresh aroma of forest or lavender.
There are also differences for men and women.
While men "refresh" with breeze vegetable extracts, so that the mattress case absorbs the heat and refreshes the body, women prefer to "heat" the case.
Red pepper extract improves blood circulation, so women feel more warmth.
The favorites currently?
Mattresses made of cold foam, which are more porous, with an adapted cell structure, making them more permeable than normal polyurethane pumps and offer more permeability.
The combination of various cold and viscoelastic foam rigidities make mattresses from various areas that taste perfectly about where the head, shoulders and heels are going.
A good quality mattress will cost you seven thousand kronor up.
Those who play a therapeutic role often have lower VAT, as they are considered as health facilities.
The first to gain this advantage in the Czech Republic was Gumotex.
It's hard to save on mattresses and somieres.
Sometimes you can approve offers from manufacturers or sellers, which sometimes offer two mattresses for the price of one.
For example, the Magniflex brand offers Duofreeze mattresses with a Memory memory foam attached to the case by 11,990 crowns.
The second is achieved for free.
The era of viscoelastic with an open cell structure and a high density began with Tempur's "cosmic" material.
Initially it emerged as material for NASA, because during astronauts take-offs were subjected to a huge overload.
Tempur softens with the heat and hardens with the cold.
Therefore, the warm human body exerts a perfect effect and optimally adapts its pressure.
Therefore, it is ideal to prevent sores from occurring, but also to improve comfort during sleep.
Vicoelastic foam is not only used on mattresses, but also for sanitary products, for example for pillows that are placed under the legs and relieve them, as well as their circulation.
National manufacturers, for example, use the Eucatherm C or Twinsaver foam and the like.
More and more parents use people tracking devices to control their children
Fear for children is increasingly leading people to think about controlling them by GPS.
The system, initially designed for vehicle tracking, can also track people's movement and contribute, for example, in case of the disappearance of the nine-year-old girl Janatková.
At the moment the device is about the size of a match box, but will soon be reduced to the size of a watch.
Many people were scared of the case of the missing Ani-ka and began reporting on the means available to better protect their children.
Even at the cost of invading your privacy.
"We all try to tell ourselves that it is not a question of spying, but another means of reducing the chances of a tragedy," says Petr Pilin of Macro Weil, one of the suppliers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
"I recognize that, in certain cases, such devices can be abused, for example if they get into someone's bag without their knowledge, but we have not yet encountered such cases."
"Most customers actually buy it for security reasons," Pilin adds.
In their view, children should always know what the "box" is for and how it is used in an emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bosková warns of the fact that, if the child does not want to carry him, he will simply throw it away.
"Even younger children show great creativity when it comes to intentionally losing certain things if they want to prevent them from being controlled."
"Before, the parents relied heavily on mobile phones, but these could be turned off as easily as the tracking device," says Bosková.
In his view, it is debatable whether such a device is really useful in the event of an attack.
"If this is a prepared abduction, the perpetrator will practically always check whether the child carries any kind of electronic device that can reveal his location."
"Now it's the phone".
"As the use of the tracking devices is extended, you will also look for them, since their sale will certainly be done with a lot of publicity."
"In such cases, criminals are always one step ahead of the police," the psychologist says.
However, he adds that such devices can help in the event of a makeshift attack by a paedophile.
According to Robert Eech of the company RC Monitoring, which offers follow-up services for both vehicles and people, even in case, after an attack, the tracking device is immediately destroyed, its presence can help.
"You can configure the device to regularly send the position after a certain period."
"If you are harmed, at least it will facilitate the last position of the person concerned."
"The most expensive devices have an inclination meter integrated, so if the person simply slips and stands still, the device will immediately issue a warning with the position in question," says Eech.
In his opinion, such a service can be obtained even with smart mobile phones with navigation, in which only special software should be installed.
The problem with current tracking units is that at the moment they are devices similar to a matchbox or smaller mobile phones.
Therefore, they may be lost.
According to Macro Weil's Pilin, for that reason tests are currently being carried out on devices that look like a digital watch.
"Furthermore, they will have the added advantage that a potential aggressor may not identify the device."
